1.)   Create a file and add executable permission to all users (user, group and others)

$ cat > module.txt                   #creating a file and adding text
Janani engineer 1234
Yamuna doctor 12345
$ ls -l module.txt                     #checking the file permission before
-rw-rw-r- - 1 ubuntu ubuntu 41 Jan 24 01:53 module.txt
$ chmod a+x module.txt       #adding executable permission for all user
$ ls -l module.txt                     # verifying the file permission after
-rwxrwxr-x 1 ubuntu ubuntu 41 Jan 24 01:53 module.txt
